radiographic_examinations.findings: Dilated appendix up to 12 mm with minimal surrounding fat stranding and no significant mucosal hyper enhancement. Innumerable hepatic hypodensities, the largest measuring up to 2.4 cm in the left lobe, likely represent cysts. No evidence of intrahepatic or extrahepatic biliary dilatation. Kidneys show bilateral hypodensities likely representing cysts. No free fluid in the pelvis.
